SIMPLE: sonometer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sonometer
<hw>So*nom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sonus</ets> a sound + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for exhibiting the transverse
vibrations of cords, and ascertaining the relations between musical
notes. It consists of a cord stretched by weight along a box, and
divided into different lengths at pleasure by a bridge, the place of
which is determined by a scale on the face of the box.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An instrument for testing the hearing
capacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sonoran</ent>⟦br⟧
